// PRONBLEM WITH contains() and solution with text locator

test("Demo", async function({ page })
{
    await page
    .setContent(`<button><span>Log</span><span>in</span></button>`)
    // await page.locator("//button[contains(text(), 'Login')]").click()
        await page.locator("text=Login").click()

    
    await page.waitForTimeout(5000)
})

These are the locators which are give by playwright:-

1) text locator

In CSS ==> no text based locator
In Xpath ==> text(), contains()           some cases wont work
In Playwright ==> text locator ==> all the cases
text() problem ==> It can identify the web element using the text
iff there is no space before and after the text, we can solve this problem usign contains()
There is still a major problem with contains(), it fails to identify text whenever the text is split across multiple tags, to overcome this problem playwrigth's text locator was invented!
